The tour of your dreams

We have a simple, yet challenging goal: to give you the best of Mid-Norway considering hiking, beautiful nature and cultural heritage. The landscape is packed with historical places and archaeological sites, and we will make sure you have professional guides.

Go Viking

Do you ever wonder how it really was like, living in the viking age? How did the food taste? What underwear were they using? Did it itch? How did they entertain themselves? How did they manage to get food and shelter?

Join us on a Viking hike in the Norwegian mountains and explore nature, survival, cooking and cultural heritage - the viking way. We’ll bring both your body and soul a thousand years back in time. And home again.

«Go Viking» will be a four day hike in Trollheimen, in the heart of Norway. This route is famous for its wild nature and is packed with cultural heritage sites dating back to the ice age. You will get the opportunity to travel Viking style; with authentic gear, clothes and shoes. Experience how man has survived in nature and discover the traces of the past. Learn how to prepare food and cook meals over an open fire, sleep under the midnight sun and join us in sharing songs and tales.

This tour is in cooperation with Hands on History.

Read more about Go Viking

Hike the Ice Age

This tour will take you a long way back in time. We’ll visit the natural wonders created by the immense ice sheet that blanketed Scandinavia for thousands of years. Everything you see around you is a result of its relentless work.

We’ll also learn about the challenges the early settlers faced, and how man has been interacting with nature over the millenias.
